{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nProve portability end-to-end: run the code_health lens against a Python client fixture AND a non-Python client fixture (Go or TS), asserting real values when analyzers are present and honest Unavailable when the `[metrics]` extra / external tools are absent. Epic headline AC.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Specify HOW the real tools become available: mark the \"present\" assertions as INTEGRATION tests gated on tool availability (skip-if-absent for scc/jscpd/npx; lizard via the `[metrics]` extra), so CI without the tools still passes and a tool-provisioned run exercises the real path.\n- Dependency text corrected to the recorded edge (depends_on 0734); adapters 18f9/21fb/3ba0 are covered transitively through 0734.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Fixtures: one Python, one non-Python (Go or TS), each with a minimal rebar ticket-store shape.\n- [ ] Analyzers present (integration, skip-if-absent): code_health computes for BOTH languages.\n- [ ] Extra/tools absent (always-run): code_health reports Unavailable for both — no crash, no fabricated data.\n- [ ] agent_process + git-delta metrics compute for both.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Interface/E2E test covering both fixtures and both present/absent states.\n\n## Dependencies: 0734 (recorded edge); transitively 18f9/21fb/3ba0.\n## Files likely touched: tests/interfaces/test_metrics_polyglot.py (new), tests/fixtures/metrics_polyglot/ (new)\n## Estimated scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784523344133665001,"uuid":"473e600b-ae9f-4e46-b6b7-94a960cd7b2b"}